 resemble the phenomenon of wraparound incarceration, in which students, despite leaving the actual detention center, cannot escape the surveillance of formal detention, and are thereby slowly pushed away from traditional schooling and a productive life course.   aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2020) 0aFemale juvenile delinquentsxCalifornia, Southern. 0aFemale juvenile delinquentszCalifornia, Southern. 0aHispanic American teenage girlsxEducation (Secondary)xCalifornia, Southern. 0aHispanic American teenage girlsxEducation (Secondary)zCalifornia, Southern. 0aHispanic American teenage girlsxSocial conditionsxCalifornia, Southern. 0aHispanic American teenage girlszCalifornia, SouthernxSocial conditions. 0aJuvenile detention homesxCalifornia, Southern. 0aJuvenile detention homeszCalifornia, Southern. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Criminology.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press eBook-Package 2016z978311066754708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press eBook-Package 2016-2018z978311063539308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUCal Press eBook Package 2014-2016z978311065748740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520960541423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780520960541.jpg  a978-3-11-063539-3  UC Press eBook-Package 2016-2018c2016d2018  a978-3-11-065748-7  UCal Press eBook Package 2014-2016c2014d2016  a978-3-11-066754-7  UC Press eBook-Package 2016b2016  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles